[^DIRECT SPEECH NOT ALWAYS DISTINGUISHABLE FROM INDIRECT SPEECH AND
OTHER LEVELS OF DISCOURSE.^]

[^IN SOME CASES, WHEN OFFERING EXTRACTS FROM DEPOSITIONS, THE SOURCE 
TEXT EDITOR INTERFERES IN THE TRANSCRIPTION BY SUPPLYING CONTEXT 
WITHOUT INDICATING IT BY THE USE OF EDITORIAL BRACKETS. THIS IS 
THE CASE WITH OUR SAMPLES 6, 7, AND 13 IN PARTICULAR.^]

